---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Nearcon 2022 — AES" bodyClass="inner-page">

  <div class="container-fluid event-hero">
    <div class="event-hero-inner">
      <div class="event-hero-left">
        <div class="event-location">Lisbon, Portugal</div>
        <div class="event-title">Nearcon<br />2022</div>
        <div class="event-tagline">
          In less than 90 days, our team transformed an abandoned Lisbon warehouse into a crypto event wonderland meets conference — produced in the middle of a hurricane, with 2,500 delegates who checked in and stayed engaged for all 3 days.
        </div>
        <div class="event-hero-photo">
          <div class="event-hero-photo-item" style="background-image: url('/images/work1.png')"></div>
          <div class="event-hero-photo-item" style="background-image: url('/images/work2.png')"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="event-hero-right">
        <div class="event-detail-card">
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">Production</div>
            <p>Our lease on the warehouse started about 10 days in advance of the event. In that time, we made roof repairs and installed all major infrastructure. After that, over 35 partners moved into their custom booths and the team at Europalco built 4 stages including 2 silent discos.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">Registration</div>
            <p>Attendees started showing up an hour early for pre-registration so we opened and were ready to go. Our registration carnival was the driest day of the event. Over the next 3 days, weather-related power and internet outages slowed registration but never stopped it. The team powered through — and without lines.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">On-Site</div>
            <p>We've never run an event through a natural disaster, but we made it work. We closed one stage for a few hours the first day but kept everything else right on track. One of the most rewarding experiences of our careers, and a great example of a client showing full trust in our team in a crisis.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid event-gallery">
    <div class="event-gallery-inner">
      <div class="gallery-grid">
        <div class="gallery-placeholder gallery-large" style="background-image: url('/images/work3.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder" style="background-image: url('/images/work5.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder" style="background-image: url('/images/work7.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder gallery-large" style="background-image: url('/images/work9.png')"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid event-back">
    <div class="event-back-inner">
      <a href="/work" class="cr-btn white ex-padding">← Back to All Events</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
